FULL NEMETIC STRING:
Φ(NonsenseProcessing) = σ(phonological_pattern|statistical_inference) ∘ ρ(human_grounding|AI_embedding) ∘ λ(experimental_probe|emergent_behavior) ∘ β(morphological_recombination|lexical_evolution) ∘ δγ(psycholinguistic_method|computational_substrate) ∘ μ(replicability|falsifiability) + ε | :divergent_cognition

OPERATOR BREAKDOWN:

σ — Air / Aerunik (emphasis: 0.82)
  Phonological pattern recognition constitutes the dominant operator. Vitevitch's
  experiments target the phonological neighborhood — the set of words differing by
  one phoneme. Humans navigate this space via articulatory-acoustic memory; ChatGPT
  navigates it via distributional statistics over token co-occurrences. The nonsense
  word acts as a null probe: it has no semantic anchor, forcing each system to reveal
  its raw pattern-matching substrate. ChatGPT's tendency to switch languages mid-task
  signals that its phonological space is not language-bounded but statistically
  continuous across training corpora.

ρ — Water / Sentaria (emphasis: 0.68)
  The relational-emotional dimension captures the felt difference between human and
  AI word-experience. Humans encounter nonsense words with embodied confusion —
  phonological forms activate motor-articulatory circuits, emotional associations,
  and childhood language-acquisition memories. AI embeddings lack this somatic
  substrate entirely. The gap is not merely computational but experiential: the same
  phonological string occupies radically different phenomenological spaces in human
  vs AI processing.

λ — Fire / Jvalion (emphasis: 0.71)
  The experimental use of nonsense words as cognitive probes represents transformative
  disruption. By removing semantic content, Vitevitch isolates the processing mechanism
  itself. ChatGPT's unexpected behaviors — defining extinct words, generating hybrid
  neologisms — are emergent properties that the probe reveals but does not cause. Fire
  here is the illumination of hidden process through deliberate destabilization of
  expected input.

β — Wood / Arboriel (emphasis: 0.55)
  Morphological recombination represents organic generative capacity. ChatGPT creates
  new words by splicing existing morphemes — a process superficially resembling human
  word-coinage but mechanistically distinct. Human neologism draws on embodied
  cultural context; AI recombination draws on statistical adjacency. The wood element
  is moderate: growth occurs, but without roots in lived experience.

δγ — Earth / Humavita (emphasis: 0.63)
  The psycholinguistic experimental method provides the grounding substrate. Vitevitch's
  decades of phonological neighborhood research anchor the AI investigation in
  established cognitive science. Earth here is the empirical tradition that makes
  the comparison legible — without human baseline data, AI behaviors would be
  uninterpretable. The computational substrate of LLMs serves as the terrain being
  mapped.

μ — Metal / Ferrosid (emphasis: 0.59)
  Structural rigor and categorical precision define the boundaries of valid inference.
  Key question: can we call ChatGPT's behavior "processing" in the same sense as
  human processing? Metal demands clear falsifiability criteria for claims about AI
  cognition. The replicability of Vitevitch's findings across different LLM versions
  and architectures remains an open structural constraint.

Z-STATE: :divergent_cognition
  Human and AI language processing converge in observable output but diverge in
  underlying mechanism. Nonsense words uniquely expose this divergence by stripping
  away the semantic overlap that normally conceals it. The system rests in a state
  of productive epistemological tension.

TENDENCY: σ → 0.82
  The phonological-analytical dimension dominates. This is fundamentally a study
  about pattern recognition — how different cognitive architectures extract and
  apply phonological regularity. All other operators serve this central inquiry.
